      <description>As the international community dithers over intervening in the Syrian civil war, one group has already planted firm roots in the country. The burgeoning al-Qaida affiliate The Support Front for the People of the Levant, known locally as Jabhat al-Nusra, has won the hearts and minds of Syrians with its battlefield heroics and moral probity. .</description>
